      • getDisplayName

        public ITextComponent getDisplayName()
        Returns a displayable component representing this thing's name. This method should be implemented slightly differently depending on the interface (for technical reasons the same method is used for both IWorldNameable and ICommandSender), but unlike Entity.getName() this method will generally behave sanely.
        INameable.getDisplayName()
        A normal component. Might be a translation component or a text component depending on the context. Usually implemented as:
        return this.hasCustomName() ? new
 TextComponentString(this.Entity.getName()) : new TextComponentTranslation(this.Entity.getName());
        ICommandSender.getDisplayName() and Entity.getDisplayName()
        For most entities, this returns the result of Entity.getName(), with scoreboard formatting and a special hover event.
        For non-entity command senders, this will return the result of Entity.getName() in a text component.
        指定者:
        getDisplayName 在接口中 ICommandSender

      • onInitialSpawn

        @Nullable
public IEntityLivingData onInitialSpawn​(DifficultyInstance difficulty,
                                        @Nullable
                                        IEntityLivingData livingdata)
        Called only once on an entity when first time spawned, via egg, mob spawner, natural spawning etc, but not called when entity is reloaded from nbt. Mainly used for initializing attributes and inventory. The livingdata parameter is used to pass data between all instances during a pack spawn. It will be null on the first call. Subclasses may check if it's null, and then create a new one and return it if so, initializing all entities in the pack with the contained data.
        覆盖:
        onInitialSpawn 在类中 EntityLiving
        参数:
        difficulty - The current local difficulty
        livingdata - Shared spawn data. Will usually be null. (See return value for more information)
        返回:
        The IEntityLivingData to pass to this method for other instances of this entity class within the same pack
